The paper deals with randomized communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The problems studied in the paper, Set Intersection and Multiple Equality Testing, involve sets and vectors, respectively, and thus could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between communication, rounds, and error probability, which is related to information theory and could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper mentions the problem of enumerating triangles in distributed networks, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
